				\begin{document}$$P_{MCT}$$\end{document} is highly dependent on the fluctuations in the marine current speed [21–23]. Two main kinds of power fluctuations can be identified: on a large time scale the generated power fluctuates over a period of 6 or 12 hours which is related to tidal astronomical phenomena; on a small time scale it can fluctuate with a period of a few seconds to several minutes shown in Fig. 1. Consequently, these fluctuations affect the power storage system which can be evaluated by:3Pss(t)=PMCT(t)-Pgrid(t)t∈P\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
