				\begin{document}$$P_{ss}$$\end{document} is defined positive during the charging period and negative during the discharge period. In order to highlight the different dynamics of the storage power flow, a fast fourier transform (FFT) is established. Figure 2 shows three scales of dynamics which obviously need different types of storage system.

According to the FFT, a hybridization of three types of storage systems corresponding to the different dynamics of power flow seems to be the best solution to deliver smooth power to the grid. In order to determine the part of each ESS, an energy management based on frequency approach is tested [24, 25]. Two low pass filters, defined in (4), are used to share out the power flow Pss\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
